args:
Ain't seen you before. We're more of
a regulars-only kind of establishment.
You're gonna want to find another spot.
Stick to the main drag.
Believe me, I'd love to. But a little bird\ntold me you might be able to point me\ntoward our mutual friend Dominic.
Oh? And you two know each\nother...how, exactly?
Let's just say that he's hanging on to\nsomething of mine, and I'm due to collect.
You lend the guy money or something?
Then you're an idiot. Whatever it was,\nkiss it goodbye. Kid's hard up for cash\ntwenty-four seven.
An old mate o' the lad you're askin' after.
He made 'imself scarce as an Ifrit egg for\na while, then aaall of a sudden 'e waltzes\nback into town with 'is pockets bulgin'.
Nope. Only thing 'e spilled was\nthat 'e found a right juicy gig.
Huh. That who was in here before, then?\nDidn't look all that fancy to me.
Aha. So you WERE holding out on me.
Ain't nothin' worth makin' a fuss over.\nGuy came in a bit ago; said he was\nDominic's boss.
I guess Dominic told him to come here if\nhe wanted to hire some muscle. Didn't\nrealize I was runnin' a damn temp agency.
Close enough. This place is always fulla\nthugs short on cash an' shorter on scruples.

You're one to talk. Anyway, he took a few
guys with him and left. You'd have to be a
total moron to buy the pitch he gave, but
my clientele ain't exactly the brightest.

He told the boys it was ＂easy work,＂ but if
you're dumb enough to ever take that kinda
thing at face value, then, well, I got
a vacation house in Hinomoto to sell ya.
He say anything specific about the job?
Something about snatching purses from\nunassuming little brats.
What?! I'm going to need you to tell me\neverything you heard. Verbatim. Now.

Easy, pal. I just did. Well, he was also
talkin' about somethin' of his getting
mixed up with some kid's bag...?
He wanted the guys to get it back.
Come on, Lathna. Let's hit that stall next!
Um...okay. But let's not go too far,\nor else Curran won't be able to\nfind us when he comes back.
Oh, right. Y'know, your dad sure is taking\nhis sweet time. What is he, part turtle?
He treats me like family, but Curran has\nhis own family. I'm...not a part of it.
You, in the yukata. You're Lathna, right?
Huh? Wh-who are you?\nHow do you know my name?
Heh heh. No need to arch yer spine, kitten.\nWe ain't gonna skin ya or nothin'.
Just hand over the purse and this'll all\ngo down sweeter than a saucer of milk.
That's for us to know and you to...not know.
Um...Lathna? Shouldn't you just give it to\nthem? It's not even yours, right?
Smart little friend ya got there.\nI suggest ya take her advice.
This could be a heretic's.\nIf I lose it...Curran will be sad!
Rrgh, the brat's runnin' for it!\nGrab her!
What do I do now?\nI have to tell someone!
WHAT? The purse-snatchers are after her?!
Got it. Thanks for the assist, kiddo.
I-I'm so sorry I couldn't help her...
Hey, don't look so down, little lady.\nI take out smellier trash than those\nthugs every morning before breakfast.
Go get yourself some rock candy from the\nstall over there. I'll have Lathna back safe\nand sound before you're even finished.
Here. Buy some for Lathna, too. I'm sure\nshe'll have worked up an appetite.
I'll wait right here. But I'm not about to eat\nmine if Lathna can't enjoy some with me.
Sounds like the three of us'll be earning\nthose cavities together, then. Hang tight.
